&lt;p&gt;To clarify, I do not play these types of games, so, though I did not test this myself, as you saw in the included video, my good friend &lt;a
  href=&#34;https://www.youtube.com/@A1RM4X/videos&#34;
    target=&#34;_blank&#34;
  &gt;&lt;strong&gt;@A1RM4X&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt; did and it seems solid enough.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;But after watching many of his streams where he was using this tool, I have noticed that it can be flaky at times, especially when game is transitioning from in-game footage to a cut-scene after killing a Boss, causing game to crash.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;That&amp;rsquo;s why I would &lt;strong&gt;Highly&lt;/strong&gt; recommend you disable it during a Boss fight, especially a big one, and re-enable it once cut-scene is over and done. That&amp;rsquo;s the only instability I have seen thus far.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Also, beware using this in &lt;strong&gt;Online-Mode&lt;/strong&gt;, I wouldn&amp;rsquo;t recommend it fearing the &lt;strong&gt;Ban-Hammer&lt;/strong&gt;. So if you do decide to use it while online and get banned, you got only yourself to blame.&lt;/p&gt;
